LeetCode 26 - Remove Duplicates from Sorted Array: 
fast scans for new unique values; slow marks the write-destination for unique values.

Input: nums = [0,0,1,1,1,2,2,3,3,4]
Output: 5 -> [0,1,2,3,4, , , , , , ]

*). i'th index inialise to 0'th position and j'th index inialise to 1'th position.
*). if i'th index value not equal to j'th index value, then we increase i'th index by 1 and store j'th index value to i'th index.
*). We return i'th + 1 beacause index start from 0'th index.

Two - Pointer's :
CODE:
class Solution {
public int removeDuplicates(int nums[]){
int n=nums.length;
int i=0, j=1;
while(j<n){
if(nums[i]!=nums[j]){
i++;
nums[i]=nums[j];
}
j++;
}
return i+1;
}
}

